      <h2 style="font-weight:700;font-family:Open Sans;color:#01498B;margin:3px 0 0 0;">Jesús Bendezú</h2>
      <h3 style="font-weight:300;text-transform:uppercase;font-family:'museo-sans';color:#008FB4;margin:3px 0 15px 0;">Project Manager</h3>
      <div class="profile" style="color:#676767;font-size:16px;letter-spacing:0.5px;"><p>A registered architect in New Mexico, where he spent over a decade practicing sustainable architecture, Jesus Bendezu has worked with pioneers of sustainable architecture and alternative construction systems, including Ed Mazria, founder of Architecture 2030; Paula Baker-Laporte; Pliny Fisk; and Gail Vittori.</p>
<p>His expertise includes non-toxic design, energy efficiency, daylighting design, passive solar design, sustainable materials and specifications, and alternative construction systems. These include adobe, straw bale, straw-clay, pumicecrete, calichecrete, compressed earthen block (CEB), and autoclaved aerated concrete (AAC).</p>
<p>Born in Peru and raised in Peru and the U. S., Jesus serves as point of contact for Brightworks clients in South America. For example, the cosmetics brand Yanbal retained Brightworks to achieve LEED certification for several facilities, and Bancolombia, the largest commercial bank in Colombia.</p>
<p>Today, in addition to his expertise in healthy design, materials specifications, and passive solar design, Jesus offers expertise in:</p>
<ul>
<li>LEED for New Construction (LEED NC)</li>
<li>LEED for Existing Buildings: Operations &amp; Maintenance (LEED EB:O&amp;M)</li>
<li>LEED for Commercial Interiors (LEED CI)</li>
<li>LEED for Core &amp; Shell (LEED CS)</li>
<li>Healthy Materials</li>
<li>Daylighting Design</li>
<li>The Natural Step (TNS)</li>
<li>California AB1103</li>
<li>CalGreen</li>
</ul>
 </div>
